      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MILE A MINUTE (3) goes very well here starting 28 times for 20 wins and seven minors. Scored by 3 lengths last time (19.10) in a Free For All over 350m at this track. Looks suited and should go close. LADY GUNAI (8) was well fancied in betting last start but could only manage one length away in second (16.54). Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Overdue and is among the main hopes. PAPA EASY (1) goes very well this course and distance starting 14 times for seven wins and five minors. In the money last time at Ballarat (25.58) in a Grade 5, finishing a 4.5 lengths third. Can hit the frame with the right run. CATCH SOME RAYS (6) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
